HEADWORD: Mesethmoid
<hw>Mes*eth"moid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mes-</ets>
+ <ets>ethmoid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to
the middle of the ethmoid region or ethmoid bone.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The median vertical plate,
or median element, of the ethmoid bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

